olive oil
1 packet pork loin steaks
1 bag baby broccoli
1 packet mashed potato
1 sachet Nan's Special Seasoning
1 packet Hollandaise
1 packet Grated Parmesan Cheese
1 packet garlic paste

• In a bowl, combine pork, Nan’s
seasoning and a drizzle of olive oil
• Heat olive oil in a frying pan over
medium-high heat. Cook pork until
cooked through, 3-4 mins each side
• Transfer to a plate to rest

• Meanwhile, trim baby broccoli
• Wipe out frying pan, then return to
medium-high heat with a drizzle of oil
• Cook baby broccoli, until tender,
4-5 mins
• Add garlic paste and cook until
fragrant, 1 min

• Meanwhile, transfer mashed potato
to a heatproof bowl
• Microwave mash until hot and
steaming, 3 mins. Stir through cheese
and season to taste
• Slice Nan’s pork
• Plate up cheesy mash, pork and
garlic veggies
• Spoon Hollandaise over pork to
serve. Enjoy!